# KiCAD Plugins Project Structure

This is a KiCAD 9.0.4 plugin collection project with the following structure:

## Core Files
- [Makefile](mdc:Makefile) - Build system for installation and cleanup
- [README.md](mdc:README.md) - Project documentation in English
- [README-j.md](mdc:README-j.md) - Project documentation in Japanese
- [LICENSE](mdc:LICENSE) - Project license

## Scripts Directory
All Python plugins and assets are located in the `scritps/` directory:
- Python scripts: `*.py` files (KiCAD plugin implementations)
- Icon files: `*.png` files (toolbar button icons)
- Design files: `*.afdesign` files (Affinity Designer source files)

## Plugin Naming Convention
- Scripts are numbered: `1_`, `2_`, `3_` etc.
- Icons follow pattern: `{function}_icon.png`
- All files use snake_case naming

## Target Installation Path
All plugins are installed to: `$(HOME)/Documents/KiCAD/9.0/scripting/plugins/`

## Build Commands
- `make install` - Install all plugins and icons
- `make clean` - Remove only project-specific files
- `make clean-all` - Remove all files from target directory